column3: “When I was a mere lad, my father warned me of the dangers of marijuana. He told me, If I catch you stealing any of MY pot
column4: I'll kick your scrawny little ass!" My father was an angry drunk with Vietnam flashbacks. He could have used some White Russian. However
column6: he would have thought it was some kind of Commie plot to steal his ditchweed. But he'd have been wrong: White Russian is a fluffy li...”"

column3: “Smoked just one bowl out of my pipe and i was gone. the high was almost instantaneous, and you could definitely tell it was a sativa dominant hybrid, but the indica was just the right amount. It kept me lit for pretty long, about 3-4 hours till i felt completely sober. definitely a great strain!”

“The only White Russian I've tried is through a local dispensary. I'm turned off by the fluffy leafy look of it. I finally gave it a shot after the selection lacked anything desirable. 

I am pleasantly shrodused by this indica dominant hybrid. I didn't realize just how strong the initial sativa onset is and wish I had known sooner. This strain reminds me of the mystery baggies from my twenties...back when a baggie wi...”

“Smoked a small bit before starting a paper for a class. Next thing 
I knew 3 hours had passed and I was ten pages in. Shit gets done man.”

“White Russian is definitely one of my favorite Sativa Dominant Hybrids. I usually smoke sativa for daytime use  because it helps with my anxiety, mental stress. This strain was able to alleviate my symptoms within minutes. Depending on the quality of the Bud, you can feel the effects instantly. The effects were euphoria, happiness, relaxation.  It helped me focus, stay active, and get things done. This strain is also...”
“Best weed i have ever tried, AMAZING saliva high, beautiful flower. The taste is an extremely smooth earthy strong taste, white widow x ak47 really is perfect.”

“I came across this strain this strain by chance - normally I get average quality herb as I live in Australia and we have no dispensaries or medicinal quality marijuana. I was very excited to try the strain after checking the reviews here.

My brother and I shared a king-sized joint after dinner, and we had to put it out 3/4 through. The flavour was fantastic; really organic, floral, and earthy tasting. I went inside ...”

“One of my favorite highs. Very uplifted feeling, which sometimes was quite energizing. I wanted to just get up and DO things constantly. Very potent with a strong head buzz and an almost psychedelic high. Very tasty as well. A top notch strain all around.”

“The minute I hit this stuff up in the bong, then Volcano Vaporizer, I could tell there was something familiar about it, not that we get great choice here in Haggis land, but it reminded me of some sort of White Widow strain, and to come on here and find out I was close I just had to join in. Lovely high, I have back issues along with anxiety, this indeed through a device such as the Volcano is fantastic, the bong hit...”

“White Russian is such a great strain. I get very extream back pain from work as well as pretty serious headaches. I decided to medicate about an hour or so before work and wow! The look of this bud is so healthy an full. One f the smoothest smokes I have ever had as well as hands down the best tasting bud I have ever smoked. My back pain was at an 8 or so and my headache was about a 6 and almost instintly they both s...”

“One of my favorite highs. Very uplifted feeling, which sometimes was quite energizing. I wanted to just get up and DO things constantly. Very potent with a strong head buzz and an almost psychedelic high. Very tasty as well. A top notch strain all around.”

“I've tried a lot of strains in my time smoking, but White Russian is one which I find quite unique.. visually it's incredibly crystally, very well-formed. It doesn't taste the greatest though, and it is crazy harsh, even out of a bong or bubbler. 

It tends to be hit me more as an indica when smoked alone, or if mixed in with other strains, seems to almost blend in (produce more sativa effects if smoked with other ...”
“when grown right it's one of the strongest i've ever had. thats the AK-47 (the russian in white russian)”

“The smell of this flower is like a florist shop in the Rainforest.  I would use it as a body wash.  Taste like ferns to me with a slight pine needle after bite.  But, the best part is how it has affected my aching arthritic body.  Three months ago I was so stiff it took half an hour to get out of bed.  Trying all of these different strains has helped so much that I am now working again lifting heavy objects.  This st...”

“This is just the weed if you want too boost your energy and keep partying all day. Very good weed to take at 4:20 am just before the sunrise! Have a pool party that starts early. Do not worry about food. Simply take your flight and feel how your journey through life gets crazier. Remember to be with the wildest people you know, and fire in the hole. Tastes in your thought as it tastes in your nose. Up beat, beach, pa...”

“I was going to write a review then I read the gold about furries masturbating furiously(say that 3 times fast) and decided there's no way I can top that piece of linguistic prowess. To be blunt this strain is dope, if you think not, I don't know what kinda weed snob you are. Ak-47 crossed with White Widow, you're going to get baked.”

“White Russian is so far one of my favorite strains of all time. After smoking it the first time, right away I felt the effects. It made me feel euphoric, energetic, talkative, my creativity was enhanced.  Great use for stress, anxiety, depression. It's more of a cerebral high. The high lasted for a long time and it helped me focus on doing some paperwork. I did not feel tired whatsoever, instead I felt extremely ener...”
“Very smoothly makes you high. The high is pretty intense, lasts very very long. Very energetic when the high ends. Very good for smoking in camp or on boat.”

“I get nostalgic every time I pick this train up which is once in a while. Before the legalization Santa Claus would leave me an ounce of this in my stocking every year as a little girl. It brings me back. I'll always have a soft spot for the strain. If you take too much you will be hanging out with an elf in your backyard.”

“Last month I had some Jack Herer,  and it was supposed to wake you up and give you energy.  This month I tried White Russian  and let me tell you.  Th EXACT opposite.   It was a mellow high that made you relax fully.  Smelt and tasted like White Widow, but brought me back to the AK days.  I highly recommend it,  no pun intended.”

“Very cerebral high with a nice sweet pine-y smell to it. Very light green with nice dark hairs to show maturity. More long and slender" Sativa look with White Widow's sugary-coat and the AK-47's Indica couch-lock properties. Great for passing around the couch watching hilarious movies or fail videos on YouTube. :)”"
“Very calm but not lazy pot. Helps pain. Makes my foot shake like crazy.”
“I just started growing these two. this pic is about six weeks into veg state.”

“AN old school HEAVY HITTER! Novices, don't do anything!DO NOT leave your bed or couch or chair or bean bag...Trying is as RSO is a must for those suffering from severe pain.  THe WR flower is alwasy gorgeous and pungent, when cultivated correctly. You'll get a little dizzy and lost in space for sure. Have fun and be careful - do not drive on this one at all! Otherwise a Godsend of a strain :)”

“When I first tried this strain I was not prepared for the potency it has. I vaped a bowl of it and as the music around me started to look plastic and my field of vision narrowed I slowly sank into the couch smiling like a clown.
I also made some edibles with White Russian"-butter and went to the opera. One of those stupid ideas you have once in a while. I can tell you this strain causes some serious acoustic halluci...”"

“Very calm but not lazy pot. Helps pain. Makes my foot shake like crazy.”

“great smelling strain, top 5 for me. definitely taste the connection to White Widow, but I enjoyed this strain more. very nice Sativa effects, Happy, euphoric, energy, after a couple bowls I forgot any aches and pains, and wanted to go out. didn't get the paranoia that widow gave me occasionally.”

“Been a while since I smoked this with a friend. All I remember is we hit it up about 4pm and we were good for the rest of the night. We were younger smokers then than we are now, but man it was a solid high! I remember wanting to talk to my buddy but we were both too into our movie of choice, Pineapple Express, to really say much and that made me a bit anxious but nothing too out of the ordinary.”

“This is one of my top favorite strains. It has that earthy flavor, gives a good head high but also just relaxes you. I totally recommend this, especially if you’re fighting depression. It’s very uplifting.”
“A very mellow high that when smoked gives a satisfying break from those persistent  headaches and migraines.”

“This is very smooth taste, but strong sleepy feeling coming after smoking. This strain makes  me happier at the same time. It takes away all thought I have, and I can focus on watching Mr. Robot". Perfect for depression

“The flowers taste a bit like spiced honey and with 25% THC, I'm cerebral but with a motivated lightness. It didn't eliminate my pain, but it smoothed out the rawness to a reasonably functional level.”
“Roll with us. Great people, on time, good product, Peter , gods gift”

“Had about a months worth of this not too long ago. The high definitely seemed to develop more shape the longer it's cured. During flowering, this pheno had a light, yet unmistakable honey smell to it. If you're growing this, I'd recommend you wait until at least 30% of the trichomes are amber, as additional CBD really compliments the high. It can be anxiety inducing if you have too much, but not as much as others. So...”

“A beautiful looking bud, very crystally, and crumbly to the touch, smells sweeter than a summers day and very prominent orange hairs. A great smoke with a bong or blunt. The high is cerebral and feels pure.”
“Stops my anxiety attacks, very calming. My head is warm and happy and full of heat.”
“This is the best strain I’ve had and I’m a daily smoker and this one sent me and I love it”

It came on with a nice heady buzz and faded into a mellow body high, still alert and capable of normal function. Smelling a bit like a rotting fruit compost with a hint of soiled diaper in the mix, this is a unique tasting stra...”

“White Russian is like killing two diseased birds with one strain. No more depression and acid reflux for me. Tasty tight dull green nugs with a lot of amber trich. Small fat sparse copper hairs. Smells like berries, pepper, lemon, and hints of pine and hops. Tastes like spicy lemon floral berries. Effects are Relaxed, sedated, happy, distracted, and a little bit of the munchies. Great strain for me, as it helps me co...”

“Amazing. Great taste and hit power. Sweet, pungent, and gives a strong pine tree scent. An uplifting high that lets you forget about all of your worries. You mellow out into a relaxing after high and stay uplifted while feeling nice body effects.”

“This strain gets you very high very quickly so you won’t need much to do the trick. I smoked a small bowl and then shared one joint with my friends and we were gone. One of the first things I noticed when I was high was how much I was laughing, I felt a very uplifting high while also feeling very relaxed and comfortable while also laughing a lot. Definitely recommend to newcomers.”
